name: Attorney General Dave Yost
tweet: Both meetings this afternoon were detailed and productive, with the legislative leaders of both caucuses asking good, informed questions.  Everyone appeared engaged and acting in good faith.  The commission has scheduled a meeting for tomorrow.

name: Attorney General Dave Yost
tweet: For the record, the Democratic members were able to have their call at 1 pm; their Republican colleagues were scheduled for 4:30 pm, and spent an hour.    With no remote participation rule yet in place, 5:30 is a bit late for them to caucus and then call for the 7:00 pm meeting.

name: Attorney General Dave Yost
tweet: We won our appeal in the Supreme Court on the Rover Pipeline case.  Bottom line: Ohio can enforce federal laws protecting our land, air and water, even if the state does not participate in granting the permit.  The decision reverses the Fifth, which threw us out of the game.
